data.text: A slide show with narration from Lee O. Triggs, a J. Walter Tompson Senior Account Executive with the 8th Marine Corps District, dedicated to John F. Kennedy, the 35th president of the United States. Triggs was sixteen years old when President Kennedy was fatally shot while riding a motorcade in Dallas. On the 50th anniversery of Kennedy's death, Triggs recites the poem he wrote on the day of the shooting. (Released/ U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Alfred Dover)
